cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with video summarization, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of tree-based models and computational aesthetics datasets suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), while the use of low-level features and segment-level features extraction may indicate cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves ranking and selection of segments, which is a common problem in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning methods and real-time processing may suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category.
